text:
Would be REALLY awesome is the VSCode extension had snippets for output html/hubl for module fields that roughly imitate the "copy snippet" function of the cloud DM.

So something like: `~image_snippet` might output:

```{% if ${field}.src %}
	{% set sizeAttrs = 'width="{{ ${field}.width }}" height="{{ ${field}.height }}"' %}
	{% if ${field}.size_type == 'auto' %}
		{% set sizeAttrs = 'style="max-width: 100%; height: auto;"' %}
	{% elif ${field}.size_type == 'auto_custom_max' %}
		{% set sizeAttrs = 'width="{{ ${field}.max_width }}" height="{{ ${field}.max_height }}" style="max-width: 100%; height: auto;"' %}
	{% endif %}
	 {% set loadingAttr = ${field}.loading != 'disabled' ? 'loading="{{ ${field}.loading }}"' : '' %}
	&lt;img src="{{ ${field}.src }}" alt="{{ ${field}.alt }}" {{ loadingAttr }} {{ sizeAttrs }}&gt;
{% endif %}```
